0-8a5e-eca7ffaa1091">22</BIBCIT> <BIBCIT DBREF="91087" PLACEHOLDER="Atwood, Shale 17" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:cbe7416a-2881-4a66-867c-ed0d141ce7b9">17</BIBCIT></BIBCITS></RRECOGNITIONS></P></SHORTPROSE></RECEPTION></DIV2><DIV2><HEADING>Animals and a Devil</HEADING><TEXTSCOPE DBREF="33950" PLACEHOLDER="MA, The Animals in That Country, 1968" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:41070adf-20b0-4a66-9a45-a9daea189b2d"/><PRODUCTION><CHRONSTRUCT RESP="IMG" CHRONCOLUMN="WRITINGCLIMATE" RELEVANCE="DECADE"><DATE VALUE="1968">1968</DATE> <CHRONPROSE><NAME STANDARD="Atwood, Margaret" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:b01b26bc-1d1f-47bf-84c9-c529c68de6f0">MA</NAME> published another volume of <TGENRE GENRENAME="POETRY">poems</TGENRE>, <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">The Animals in That Country</TITLE>, this time with <ORGNAME STANDARD="Oxford University Press" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:6ad3f7c1-b263-42cd-bfe2-e864ddecf761">Oxford University Press</ORGNAME> in <PLACE><SETTLEMENT>Toronto</SETTLEMENT><REGION REG="Ontario"/><GEOG REG="Canada"/></PLACE>.</CHRONPROSE><BIBCITS/></CHRONSTRUCT></PRODUCTION><TEXTUALFEATURES><SHORTPROSE><P><TVOICENARRATION>In this collection she regularly makes the leap from a human to an animal (and therefore a disempowered and disenfranchised) point of view: <QUOTE DIRECT="Y">and I'm dragged to the mind's / dead-end, the roar of the bone- / yard.</QUOTE><BIBCITS/></TVOICENARRATION></P></SHORTPROSE></TEXTUALFEATURES></DIV2><DIV2><PRODUCTION><SHORTPROSE><P><PMATERIALCONDITIONS><PPERIODICALPUBLICATION>While writer-in-residence at the English Department of the <ORGNAME STANDARD="University of Alberta" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:6a9d995b-4cd6-460f-9c55-7e83669ad6a8">University of Alberta</ORGNAME>, <NAME STANDARD="Atwood, Margaret" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:b01b26bc-1d1f-47bf-84c9-c529c68de6f0">MA</NAME> contributed to the department's short-lived periodical called <TITLE TITLETYPE="JOURNAL">The Merry Devil of Ed