: for example <QUOTE DIRECT="Y">Longed for him. Got him. Shit.</QUOTE><BIBCITS/></TGENREISSUE></P></SHORTPROSE></PRODUCTION></DIV2></DIV1><DIV1><HEADING>For Children</HEADING><DIV2><PRODUCTION><CHRONSTRUCT RESP="JEB" CHRONCOLUMN="WRITINGCLIMATE" RELEVANCE="SELECTIVE"><DATE VALUE="1978-06" CERTAINTY="BY">By June 1978</DATE> <CHRONPROSE><NAME STANDARD="Atwood, Margaret" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:b01b26bc-1d1f-47bf-84c9-c529c68de6f0">MA</NAME> published her first <TGENRE GENRENAME="CHILDRENSLITERATURE">children's book</TGENRE>, a volume of <TGENRE GENRENAME="POETRY">poetry</TGENRE> for young readers entitled <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Up in the Tree</TITLE>.</CHRONPROSE> <BIBCITS><BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="BRI 1: 225" DBREF="1704" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:a11d152f-ac54-417a-8de8-99356a7b5f51">1: 225</BIBCIT></BIBCITS></CHRONSTRUCT><SHORTPROSE><P><PEDITIONS>This was translated by <NAME STANDARD="Caillol, Michel" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:0878c62a-b445-4ffc-b747-9aa5601a5070">Michel Caillol</NAME> as <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC" REG="Up in the Tree">Sur l'arbre perchés</TITLE>, <PLACE><SETTLEMENT>Montreal</SETTLEMENT><REGION REG="Quebec"/><GEOG REG="Canada"/></PLACE>, 1979.</PEDITIONS></P></SHORTPROSE></PRODUCTION><TEXTUALFEATURES><SHORTPROSE><P>The book has a story-line. <TPLOT>The children get up the tree by means of a ladder, and are stuck when someone takes it away, but later <TMOTIF MOTIFNAME="rescue">rescue</TMOTIF>d.</TPLOT></P></SHORTPROSE></TEXTUALFEATURES><PRODUCTION><SHORTPROSE><P><DATE VALUE="1980">Two years later</DATE> <NAME STANDARD="Atwood, Margaret" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:b01b26bc-1d1f-47bf-84c9-c529c68de6f0">MA</NAME> collaborated with her aunt <NAME STANDARD="Barkhouse, Joyce" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:51f01203-2ed2-44d3-a977-142e98a122f5">Joyce Barkhouse</NAME> on another work for children, <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Anna's Pet</TITLE> (in the <TITLE TITLETYPE="SERIES">Kids in Canada</TITL