"><TSETTINGPLACE SETTINGPLACETYPE="REAL" SETTINGCLASS="WIDERANGE">The book opens on Iris receiving the news of Laura's death by <TMOTIF MOTIFNAME="suicide">suicide</TMOTIF>, ten days after the end of World War Two, by driving her car off a bridge into a <PLACE><SETTLEMENT>Toronto</SETTLEMENT><REGION REG="Ontario"/><GEOG REG="Canada"/></PLACE> ravine. Iris, having confronted the bad-news-bringing policeman with overt hostility and hidden grief and rage, goes to find gloves and a handkerchief to take to the morgue, and <TMOTIF MOTIFNAME="found manuscript">finds the novel hidden in her drawer, in exercise books tied up with string</TMOTIF>. It concerns a romance, during the harsh years of the depression, between a privileged girl and a man from the lower class, writer of low-grade science fiction.</TSETTINGPLACE></TSETTINGDATE> <TSETTINGPLACE SETTINGPLACETYPE="FICTIVE">Important among his courtship techniques is the gradual relaying of his <TGENRE GENRENAME="FANTASY">fantasy</TGENRE> story in which the blind assassins are a class of people, their eyesight deliberately ruined by close work as young children, who are used on the planet Zycron for various menial tasks including hired killing.</TSETTINGPLACE> This unfinished story is subject to constant negotiation between the lovers, with the man favouring heavy <TTHEMETOPIC>technology</TTHEMETOPIC> and a death-dominated ending, while the woman leans towards emphasis on emotions and a <TMOTIF MOTIFNAME="happy ending">happy ending</TMOTIF>.</P></SHORTPROSE></TEXTUALFEATURES><RECEPTION><SHORTPROSE><P><RRECOGNITIONS>This novel won Atwood the <RRECOGNITIONNAME>Booker Prize</RRECOGNITIONNAME>, in addition to being short-listed for other prestigious prizes. <NAME STANDARD="Tremain, Rose" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:a13442a2-cb4c-447e-85cf-79ff47305e6f">Rose Tremain</NAME>, doing her second stint as a Booker judge, later revealed that nobody on the panel thought this Atwood's best book, but they all thought she deserved