3-2431-4a66-8048-2aefe3909cd6">Twitter</ORGNAME> and by March 2015 had had 698K followers, as well as 178,734 likes on <ORGNAME STANDARD="Facebook" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:3688bafe-7a66-47c0-b77c-ccb1219e557a">Facebook</ORGNAME>.</PCIRCULATION> She has published (<TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC" REG="In Other Worlds: SF and the Human Imagination">In Other Worlds</TITLE>, 2011) on the sustainable straw paper which is aiming in time to replace woodpulp paper. <PSERIALIZATION><PAUTHORSHIP COLLABORATION="COLLABORATIONYES">She has collaborated with British writer <NAME STANDARD="Alderman, Naomi" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:f57418c4-8808-4f55-8c82-32b2187a6b4b">Naomi Alderman</NAME> on <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">The Happy Zombie Sunrise Home</TITLE>, published serially on the digital platform <ORGNAME STANDARD="Wattpad" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:f44ef385-320f-452e-896d-694b8d13ecd8">Wattpad</ORGNAME>.</PAUTHORSHIP> Much of her work is available in e-book form, and she has also published solely on <ORGNAME STANDARD="Kindle" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:12a1d2fd-7e96-44a5-8985-cc30a1495be5">Kindle</ORGNAME> with no paper edition (as by now a number of established authors have done): her <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Positron</TITLE>, serially published on Kindle by <ORGNAME STANDARD="Byliner Fiction" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:0797fba3-f730-485a-9286-c0722fdc0bae">Byliner</ORGNAME>, began with <TITLE TITLETYPE="ANALYTIC">I'm Starved for You</TITLE> (March 2012) and ended with <TITLE TITLETYPE="ANALYTIC">The Heart Goes Last</TITLE> (June 2013).</PSERIALIZATION><BIBCITS/></P></SHORTPROSE></PRODUCTION><TEXTUALFEATURES><SHORTPROSE><P><TTONESTYLE><TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">The Happy Zombie Sunrise Home</TITLE> is funny as well as dark.</TTONESTYLE> <TSETTINGDATE SETTINGDATETYPE="FUTURE"><TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Positron</TITLE> is a <TGENRE GENRENAME="DYSTOPIA">dystopian</TGENRE> <TGENRE GENRENAME="NOVEL">novel</TGE