nd <TMOTIF MOTIFNAME="illness">victims of disease are shut up for life</TMOTIF> in a <SOCALLED>Freeforall</SOCALLED> or prison site of permanent orgies with no exit. It follows that in this society the prospect of marriage is terrifying.</TSETTINGDATE></P></SHORTPROSE></TEXTUALFEATURES></DIV2><DIV2><HEADING><TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Angel Catbird</TITLE></HEADING><TEXTSCOPE DBREF="89570" PLACEHOLDER="MA, Angel Catbird, 2016" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:cd94c8fc-2b1d-48f8-894c-864d6ad04c4b"/><PRODUCTION><CHRONSTRUCT CHRONCOLUMN="WRITINGCLIMATE" RELEVANCE="PERIOD" RESP="IMG"><DATE VALUE="2016-09-06">6 September 2016</DATE> <CHRONPROSE><NAME STANDARD="Atwood, Margaret" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:b01b26bc-1d1f-47bf-84c9-c529c68de6f0">MA</NAME>, in collaboration with the artist <NAME STANDARD="Christmas, Johnnie" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:bad9e142-e425-401f-b709-e08034b21d51">Johnnie Christmas</NAME> and the colourist <NAME STANDARD="Bonvillain, Tamra" REF="https://commons.cwrc.ca/orlando:ea6a21bf-3985-4d9f-b42c-6659421eae1e">Tamra Bonvillain</NAME>, published a <TGENRE GENRENAME="COMICBOOK">comic book</TGENRE> entitled <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Angel Catbird</TITLE>.</CHRONPROSE><BIBCITS/></CHRONSTRUCT><SHORTPROSE><P>She observed that this creation was foreshadowed long since: as a child she was constantly drawing winged cats as superheroes; later she was enthralled by <QUOTE DIRECT="Y">the huge outburst of comic books in the late 1940s</QUOTE>; and in the 1970s she created and wrote a strip called <TITLE TITLETYPE="SERIES">Kanadian Kultchur Komix</TITLE> in <TITLE TITLETYPE="JOURNAL">This Magazine</TITLE>.</P></SHORTPROSE></PRODUCTION><TEXTUALFEATURES><SHORTPROSE><P>The book's hero, <TCHARACTERNAME>Strig Feleedus</TCHARACTERNAME>, a <TCHARACTERTYPEROLE PROTAGONIST="MALE">young genetic engineeer</TCHARACTERTYPEROLE>, has had his <TTHEMETOPIC>DNA experimentally crossed</TTHEMETOPIC> with those of a cat and an owl. Statistics from <